OL,3,CAbortion buffer zone legislation not
OL,4,Cenforceable when clinics closed,
OL,5,Cpolice say
OL,7,F"For any particular activity to be an
OL,8,Foffence, it must, for example, be
OL,9,Fcapable of influencing someone's
OL,10,Fdecision to access or provide abortion
OL,11,Fservices or impede someone's access to
OL,12,Fsuch services.
OL,14,F"An act carried out which has an
OL,15,Fimpact within the zone when a clinic
OL,16,Fis closed, but which could continue to
OL,17,Fhave that impact once services are
OL,18,Fopen, could give rise to an offence.
